I am going to pick Perl for homework - 1

This first simple function demonstrates Perl hash of arrays.

invert_hash function creates inverted hash, with keys from input hash values and values from input hash keys.

I have used key & values from this page http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secondary_color to show this example.

function1.pl

The output would be

green = yellow cyan
blue = cyan magenta
red = yellow magenta



