This second simple function demonstrates tr (Perl transliteration operator)

vowel_upper function converts lowercase vowel characters to uppercase vowel characters.

I have used myrrh (word without vowels), eau (word consisting of only vowels) to show this example.

function2.pl


The output would be

EAU dE cOlOgnE myrrh


